From Mike Sprague Subject Re Soundblaster IRQ and Port settings My solution was to switch the interrupt to IRQ which is unreserved in contemporary computers using IRQ for the drives went out with the XT architechture Not completly For AT class and later machines is reserved for Since it's rare to have a second parallel port in a PC it's usually a good safe choice if you need an On the other hand we just ran into a problem with that here at work on a Gateway computer It has a Modem on a Mouse on and the other serial port was set to which normally uses the same interrupt as We had a real fight with a board when trying to use and discoverd the problem was that Gateway had set it up such that used As soon as we disabled our problems went Grumble after several days of trying to figure out why the interrupt didn't Mike